6012:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h **** /**
6013:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @brief  Set ADC analog watchdog thresholds value of both thresholds
6014:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         high and low.
6015:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If value of only one threshold high or low must be set,
6016:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         use function @ref LL_ADC_SetAnalogWDThresholds().
6017:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   In case of ADC resolution different of 12 bits,
6018:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         analog watchdog thresholds data require a specific shift.
6019:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Use helper macro @ref __LL_ADC_ANALOGWD_SET_THRESHOLD_RESOLUTION().
6020:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, there are 2 kinds of analog watchdog
6021:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         instance:
6022:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD standard (instance AWD1):
6023:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: can monitor 1 channel or all channels.
6024:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: ADC groups regular and-or injected.
6025:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is not limited (corresponds to
ARM GAS  C:\Users\ChipTec\AppData\Local\Temp\ccMHUsU7.s 			page 112


6026:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             ADC resolution configured).
6027:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD flexible (instances AWD2, AWD3):
6028:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: flexible on channels monitored, selection is
6029:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             channel wise, from from 1 to all channels.
6030:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Specificity of this analog watchdog: Multiple channels can
6031:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             be selected. For example:
6032:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             (LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL4_REG_INJ | LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL5_REG_INJ | ...)
6033:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: not selection possible (monitoring on both
6034:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             groups regular and injected).
6035:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Channels selected are monitored on groups regular and injected:
6036:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG_INJ (do not use parameters
6037:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG and LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_INJ)
6038:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is limited to 8 bits: if ADC resolution is
6039:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             12 bits the 4 LSB are ignored, if ADC resolution is 10 bits
6040:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             the 2 LSB are ignored.
6041:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If ADC oversampling is enabled, ADC analog watchdog thresholds are
6042:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         impacted: the comparison of analog watchdog thresholds is done on
6043:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         oversampling final computation (after ratio and shift application):
6044:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC data register bitfield [15:4] (12 most significant bits).
6045:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Examples:
6046:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
6047:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 12 bits (ratio 16 and shift 4, or ratio 32 and shift 5, ...):
6048:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 16.
6049:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
6050:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 14 bits (ratio 16 and shift 2, or ratio 32 and shift 3, ...):
6051:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 4.
6052:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
6053:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 16 bits (ratio 16 and shift none, or ratio 32 and shift 1, ...):
6054:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds match directly to ADC data register.
6055:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, setting of this feature is conditioned to
6056:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC state:
6057:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC must be disabled or enabled without conversion on going
6058:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         on either groups regular or injected.
6059:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @rmtoll TR1      HT1            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
6060:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         TR2      HT2            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
6061:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         TR3      HT3            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
6062:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         TR1      LT1            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
6063:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         TR2      LT2            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds\n
6064:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         TR3      LT3            LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds
6065:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  ADCx ADC instance
6066:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDy This parameter can be one of the following values:
6067:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD1
6068:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD2
6069:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         @arg @ref LL_ADC_AWD3
6070:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDThresholdHighValue Value between Min_Data=0x000 and Max_Data=0xFFF
6071:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @param  AWDThresholdLowValue Value between Min_Data=0x000 and Max_Data=0xFFF
6072:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @retval None
6073:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h ****   */
6074:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_ll_adc.h **** __STATIC_INLINE void LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds(ADC_TypeDef *ADCx, uint32_t AWDy, uint32_t AWD
